# Changed a large part of it since the asakim "lore" rework
ghost-role-information-asakim-name = Asakim Unit
ghost-role-information-asakim-description = A genetically and cybernetically enhanced supersoldier, stranded in the sector after a bluespace incident.
ghost-role-information-asakim-rules =
    You are a [color=yellow][bold]Free-Agent[/bold][/color]. You are to pursue your objectives. But you can also socialize with the members of the sector while doing so.
    You have [color=red]no knowledge[/color] (maybe basic at most) [color=red]of this sector of space, its inhabitants, its factions, or its culture[/color]. While you cannot speak their language, you can understand it.
    You may kill your targets if you have any, and you may kill to defend yourself and your property. [color=green]Civilians and the innocent are not your enemy[/color], and may be useful to you. Fight with honor.
    You have a integrated radio implant to communicate with fellow Asakim on. (Use :j )
    You do not concern yourself with the matters of this sector, as you will probably get back to your era before any of these significantly affect you. Only retaliate when attacked.
asakim-role-briefing =
    You are an Asakim, a genetically and cybernetically enhanced soldier from a different era.
    You’ve awoken from long-term cryosleep in an unfamiliar sector and time.
    Contact with the AI commanding your unit has been cut.
    Your objective is to try and find resources to return to your time, ideally nonlethally.
